<subSubSection id="C36F0AA4FFBFCC7BA38CBF9BFDD9FEC0" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="193" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCA592FFFBFCC7BA38CBF9BFDD9FEC0" blockId="41.[151,1436,1448,2014]" lastBlockId="42.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="193" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBFCC78A38CBF9BFEF2F8A3" bold="true" box="[199,308,1772,1798]" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">Remarks</emphasis>
: Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBFCC78A2F5BF9BFD11F8A3" authority="Kokujev" authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1906" box="[446,727,1772,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eremita">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBFCC78A2F5BF9BFDA9F8A3" box="[446,623,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">Ophion eremita</emphasis>
Kokujev
</taxonomicName>
but distinguished by the less numerous flagellomeres (44‒50) (44 and 
<quantity id="4C8DF4CAFFBFCC78A3BEBE67FEF6F88F" box="[245,304,1808,1834]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1684" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" unit="in" value="46.0">46 in</quantity>
the studied types of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBFCC78A155BE67FD1FF88F" authorityName="Szepligeti" authorityYear="1905" box="[542,729,1808,1834]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turcomanicus">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBFCC78A155BE67FD1FF88F" box="[542,729,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">O. turcomanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity id="4C8DF4CAFFBFCC78A1A3BE67FCE5F88F" box="[744,803,1808,1835]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" unit="in" value="50.0">50 in</quantity>
the type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBFCC78A0E6BE67FBF3F88F" authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1906" box="[941,1077,1808,1834]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiaticus">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBFCC78A0E6BE67FBF3F88F" box="[941,1077,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">O. asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the often complete, but rather weak carination of propodeum, which usually have at least the anterior and posterior transverse carinae present and the area superomedial discernible. The mandibles, which are often worn, are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBFCC78A7EEBE2FFAA4F8D7" box="[1189,1378,1880,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slaviceki">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBFCC78A7EEBE2FFAA4F8D7" box="[1189,1378,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">Ophion slaviceki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with an acute angled gap without internal angles and thereby differing from the mandibles of 
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBFCC78A731BE0BFB3EF833" box="[1146,1272,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBFCC78A731BE0BFB32F833" authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1906" box="[1146,1268,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eremita">O. eremita</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which usually have distinct internal angles in a right-angled gap. On average also smaller than 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBFCC78A705BED7FB0EF81F" authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1906" box="[1102,1224,1952,1978]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eremita">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBFCC78A705BED7FB0EF81F" box="[1102,1224,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">O. eremita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The here studied specimens display a considerable amount of variation which may indicate cryptic species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBFCC78A7E5BEB3FAACF87B" authorityName="Szepligeti" authorityYear="1905" box="[1198,1386,1988,2014]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turcomanicus">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBFCC78A7E5BEB3FAACF87B" box="[1198,1386,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="192">O. turcomanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBCCC7BA3DCB9E0FED6FF15" authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1906" box="[151,272,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eremita">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBCCC7BA3DCB9E0FED6FF15" box="[151,272,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">O. eremita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to an aggregate of similar and closely related desert and steppe species also including 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBCCC7BA603B9E0FE53FF70" authority="Habemehl, 1921" authorityName="Habemehl" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geyri">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBCCC7BA603B9E0FF17FF71" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Ophion geyri</emphasis>
Habemehl, 1921
</taxonomicName>
and a couple of undescribed species. Of particular interest is a single female in coll. MR with unusually large ocelli and weakly defined pleurosternal angles. This specimen corresponds with the 
<typeStatus id="54CEE78DFFBCCC7BA671B9A8FA5AFF5C" box="[1338,1436,223,249]" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBCCC7BA3FDB874FD18FEB8" authority="Hedwig, 1961" authorityName="Hedwig" authorityYear="1961" box="[182,734,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="obscuratus" variety="heratensis">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBCCC7BA3FDB874FE4BFEB8" box="[182,397,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Ophion obscuratus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBCCC7BA28EB874FDFEFEB8" box="[453,568,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">heratensis</emphasis>
Hedwig, 1961
</taxonomicName>
housed in the SMNK. It is here treated as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFBCCC7BA603B874FEE8FEE5" authorityName="Szepligeti" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turcomanicus">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFBCCC7BA603B874FEE8FEE5" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="193">Ophion turcomanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but if this form is found to be a valid species, it has to be assigned a new name given the fact that it was described as a variety in 1961.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
